               <msContents>
                  <summary>F. 1: Arabic jottings and drafts of sentences for documents, including the name Al-Qādī Abū Ẓāhir. F. 2r: writing exercises with the Hebrew alphabet. F. 2v: copy of a document dated Jumādā I, 589 AH (= May-June 1193 CE) appointing Abū l-Maʿālī ʿAbdallāh b. Abū l-Riḍāʿ b. Faraḥ, who is known by his Jewish name Obadiah b. ʿUlla, as the Jewish leader in Syria issued by the court of Al-Malik al-Afḍal ʿAlī (the eldest son of Saladin). The document praises Obadiah and states that Obadiah will be the head of Rabbanites, Karaites and Samaritans in the Damascus area.</summary>
                  <msItem n="1">                           

                     <title>Legal document; pen trials</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="heb">Arabic; Hebrew</textLang>
